column2: Good afternoon! ...Or should I say "evening"? Morning...morning?
At any rate, I am the game master.
Before we begin, there is something I must tell you.
You see, my job is to draw you into this world with my voice and cards.
Which is why I believe it best for you to play with the sound on.
In fact, I insist on it!
As you can see, my voice is subtitled, so you can always read along as well.
Pay attention because this is important.
Maybe you should come back if you ever find a key.
If you do, I'm sure something good will happen...
Well, it is your choice after all.
Isn't it dangerous to go without a torch?
Perhaps you should use your torch card here.
If you don't have a torch, pray consider turning back for now...
I cannot in all good conscience let you continue without a torch.
"Leave Now" would be the fastest way out.
Though I suppose all I do is move the piece around...
I suppose there's nothing wrong with that. To each their own.
You never miss a chance to earn some coin, do you?
That girl is in a world of her own.
Let's head to Unionville first, shall we?
It seems even monsters have their problems...
I should have seen that one coming.
Though I understand your urge to hurry on ahead...
I think you made the right choice.
Careful! He won't go down easy!
Lower Mr. Flobby's stamina to calm him down.
Saving one forsakes the other... What a cruel world this is.
You won't catch a spryfish swimming out there.
Hurry to the wharf to find the spryfish.
Are you serious about finding the spryfish...?
It's kill or be killed, I suppose.
Looks like it's too early to come this way.
You've got a long road ahead of you, so you had best be prepared.
You've spent so long in here, even I'm starting to sweat...
Take your time. There's no need to rush yet.
You might want to pick up the pace about now.
Let's return here in a bit.
The path to the Mausoleum is a long one.
If you start feeling weary on your journey, use the Jump feature to return to the village.
I wouldn't be surprised if it's ghooosts considering where we are...
It felt like that knight wanted to stop you from going any further.
Why not check the wall around here?
There may be something on the wall nearby...
Once you go in there, you won't be able to save. Proceed with caution.
Think long and hard about this one...
Like I said, you can't walk on water.
Try all you like, but you still can't walk on water.
You can't go in there. That's the ocean.
You can't go in the ocean.
Why are you so eager for a swim? It's not going to happen.
You won't be able to climb that mountain. You'll have to take the long way around.
Not even a rock climber could get up those steep cliffs.
Wake me up when you need me...
It feels like watching a bodybuilder competition!
It looks like it won't put up a fight.
It'll take more than numbers to win here.
Luck is on your side today.
Don't worry. The coffin card is down, but they're still alive.
It looks like your adventure ends here...
The One Who Wanted It All
